sql:
SELECT DISTINCT state_code
FROM agricultural_data
ORDER BY state_code;

external_knowledge:
External knowledge needed to understand this question includes: 
- State hierarchy refers to the recursive relationship where some states may also serve as regions for other states; 
- Agricultural export data is assumed to be collected annually and includes a total export value for each state; 
- User access patterns refer to the frequency of system access by individual users; 
- Report generation statistics include the quantity and timing of reports generated relative to the start of the year.

sql:
SELECT MAX(total_exports) AS max_total_exports
FROM agricultural_data
WHERE state_code = 'AK';

SELECT DISTINCT region
FROM states
ORDER BY region;

SELECT SUM(total_exports) AS total_annual_exports
FROM agricultural_data
WHERE year = 2023;
